---
const alerts = [
	{
		id: 1,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-001',
		title: 'Suspicious Shell Execution by Backup Rotation Job',
		host: 'ORION-WEB',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T08:18:55Z',
		correct: 'false',
		explanation:
			'False Positive. The observed activity corresponds to backup-rotate --version and normal backup tasks. The alert suggests possible shell execution, but there is no evidence that backup-rotate launched sh, bash, or dash as a child process. Because the parent/child relationship that would confirm the alert is missing, it is classified as a false positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ORION-WEB" and process.name: "backup-rotate"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000001',
	},
	{
		id: 2,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-002',
		title: 'Command Execution from CMS Plugin Directory',
		host: 'ORION-WEB',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T08:36:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. The evidence shows that the nginx/php-fpm web context launched dash with sh -c id from a CMS plugin directory. This combination of web user, php-fpm8.2 parent process, working directory under plugins, and command execution confirms suspicious activity.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ORION-WEB" and process.name: "dash"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000003; AUR-EVT-000004; AUR-EVT-000005',
	},
	{
		id: 3,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-003',
		title: 'Local Account Enumeration from Web Context',
		host: 'ORION-WEB',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T08:41:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. The nginx user executed commands such as cat /etc/passwd and ls -la /home/elena. Enumerating accounts and user directories from a web context is not normal application behavior, so the alert is confirmed.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ORION-WEB" and process.command_line: (*passwd* or */home/elena*)',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000006; AUR-EVT-000007',
	},
	{
		id: 4,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-004',
		title: 'Suspicious Access to User SSH Material',
		host: 'ORION-WEB',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T08:46:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. There is evidence of access to /home/elena/.ssh, including listing or reading SSH material from a web context. A process associated with nginx should not inspect SSH keys or SSH directories belonging to local users, so this case is a true positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ORION-WEB" and file.path: */home/elena/.ssh*',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000008; AUR-EVT-000009',
	},
	{
		id: 5,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-005',
		title: 'Unusual Outbound Connection from Web Service',
		host: 'ORION-WEB',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T08:50:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. php-fpm8.2 made outbound connections to 10.10.22.45 after command execution on the web server. An outbound connection from a web process to a suspicious IP address on unusual ports confirms the alert.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ORION-WEB" and destination.ip: "10.10.22.45"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000010',
	},
	{
		id: 6,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-006',
		title: 'Suspicious Command Execution by Build Service',
		host: 'FORGE-CI',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T09:03:55Z',
		correct: 'false',
		explanation:
			'False Positive. The command df -k /opt/forgeci/workspace was executed by builder as a normal CI service check. There is no use of /tmp, sudo, credential access, payload, or suspicious command chain. For that reason, it is dismissed as a false positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "FORGE-CI" and process.command_line: "df -k /opt/forgeci/workspace"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000012',
	},
	{
		id: 7,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-007',
		title: 'Suspicious Access to Shell History',
		host: 'FORGE-CI',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T09:18:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. The builder user read /home/builder/.bash_history from an interactive shell. Access to shell history can reveal commands, sensitive paths, or secrets accidentally typed into the shell, so the alert is confirmed.',
		kql: 'host.name: "FORGE-CI" and file.path: */.bash_history',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000014',
	},
	{
		id: 8,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-008',
		title: 'Possible Local Privilege Escalation Discovery',
		host: 'FORGE-CI',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T09:23:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. builder executed sudo -l from an interactive shell. This command is used to discover available sudo privileges and, in this context, is part of local reconnaissance activity. It is classified as a true positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "FORGE-CI" and process.command_line: "sudo -l"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000016',
	},
	{
		id: 9,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-009',
		title: 'Executable Permission Added to Temporary File',
		host: 'FORGE-CI',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T09:29:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. builder executed chmod +x on a file located in /tmp, and related activity appears afterward. Adding execute permissions to a temporary file is a strong indicator of preparation for suspicious execution.',
		kql: 'host.name: "FORGE-CI" and process.command_line: *chmod* and process.working_directory: "/tmp"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000018',
	},
	{
		id: 10,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-010',
		title: 'Multiple Outbound Connections by Package Service',
		host: 'ATLAS-MAIL',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T09:42:55Z',
		correct: 'false',
		explanation:
			'False Positive. The connections were made by apt-helper or unattended-upgrade to package mirrors over ports 80/443. There are no suspicious commands nearby, unusual destinations, or relationship with unauthorized access activity. This is normal update traffic.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ATLAS-MAIL" and process.name: ("apt-helper" or "unattended-upgrade")',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000020; AUR-EVT-000021; AUR-EVT-000022',
	},
	{
		id: 11,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-011',
		title: 'Suspicious IMAP Authentication Failures',
		host: 'ATLAS-MAIL',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T09:59:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. Multiple IMAP authentication failures were observed from 10.10.22.45 against port 993. Repeated attempts from the same IP address against a mail service indicate suspicious authentication activity, so the alert is true.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ATLAS-MAIL" and destination.port: 993 and source.ip: "10.10.22.45"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000024; AUR-EVT-000025; AUR-EVT-000026; AUR-EVT-000027; AUR-EVT-000028; AUR-EVT-000029',
	},
	{
		id: 12,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-012',
		title: 'Automation Script Executed as Root',
		host: 'ATLAS-MAIL',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T10:14:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. root executed /home/mateo/.mail-sync.sh, and child actions such as tar or rm were observed afterward. Root executing a script located in a user profile is anomalous and enough to confirm the alert.',
		kql: 'host.name: "ATLAS-MAIL" and process.command_line: */home/mateo/.mail-sync.sh*',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000030; AUR-EVT-000031',
	},
	{
		id: 13,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-013',
		title: 'Possible Anonymous SMB Enumeration',
		host: 'LYRA-FS',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T10:31:55Z',
		correct: 'false',
		explanation:
			'False Positive. An anonymous SMB logon exists, but it is an isolated event and there is no follow-up evidence of share enumeration, remote execution, multiple failures, lateral movement, or relevant activity afterward. Without additional evidence, it is classified as a false positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "LYRA-FS" and user.name: "ANONYMOUS LOGON"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000033',
	},
	{
		id: 14,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-014',
		title: 'Possible SMB Password Spraying',
		host: 'LYRA-FS',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T10:46:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. Several 4625 events with LogonType 3 were observed from 10.10.22.45 against multiple SMB users. The combination of the same source, multiple users, and repeated failures matches a password spraying pattern.',
		kql: 'host.name: "LYRA-FS" and event.code: "4625" and source.ip: "10.10.22.45"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000035; AUR-EVT-000036; AUR-EVT-000037; AUR-EVT-000038; AUR-EVT-000039; AUR-EVT-000040',
	},
	{
		id: 15,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-015',
		title: 'Suspicious Access to PowerShell History',
		host: 'VEGA-WS',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T11:03:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. PowerShell read ConsoleHost_history.txt and searched for password-related strings. Searching PowerShell history can reveal credentials or sensitive commands, so it is considered a true positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "VEGA-WS" and process.command_line: *ConsoleHost_history.txt*',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000041',
	},
	{
		id: 16,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-016',
		title: 'Privileged Account Login from Suspicious Source',
		host: 'NOVA-ADM',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T11:19:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. A 4624 LogonType 10 login for Administrator was observed from 10.10.22.45, followed by special privilege assignment. A privileged RDP login from a suspicious source confirms the alert.',
		kql: 'host.name: "NOVA-ADM" and event.code: "4624" and winlog.event_data.LogonType: "10"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000043; AUR-EVT-000044',
	},
	{
		id: 17,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-017',
		title: 'Executable Created in User AppData Directory',
		host: 'NOVA-ADM',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T11:25:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. PowerShell created C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Local\\syncsvc.exe. Creating an executable in AppData under an administrator profile, especially after a suspicious login, is clear evidence of anomalous activity.',
		kql: 'host.name: "NOVA-ADM" and file.path: *AppData\\\\Local\\\\syncsvc.exe',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000045; AUR-EVT-000046',
	},
	{
		id: 18,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-018',
		title: 'Suspicious Scheduled Task Using User Profile Path',
		host: 'NOVA-ADM',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T11:29:55Z',
		correct: 'true',
		explanation:
			'True Positive. Event 4698 shows the creation of the \\SystemSyncCheck task, pointing to the syncsvc.exe executable inside Administrator AppData. A scheduled task that runs binaries from a user profile is suspicious and confirms persistence.',
		kql: 'host.name: "NOVA-ADM" and event.code: "4698" and winlog.event_data.TaskName: "\\\\SystemSyncCheck"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000047',
	},
	{
		id: 19,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-019',
		title: 'rundll32.exe Executing DLL with Unusual Arguments',
		host: 'NOVA-ADM',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T11:46:55Z',
		correct: 'false',
		explanation:
			'False Positive. rundll32.exe executed shell32.dll from C:\\Windows\\System32 with explorer.exe as the parent process and normal COM arguments. There is no DLL in a suspicious path, encoded PowerShell, or associated payload. For that reason, it is a false positive.',
		kql: 'host.name: "NOVA-ADM" and process.name: "rundll32.exe"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000049',
	},
	{
		id: 20,
		code: 'AUR-ALERT-020',
		title: 'Suspicious Process Access to LSASS',
		host: 'VEGA-WS',
		timestamp: '2025-07-18T12:01:55Z',
		correct: 'false',
		explanation:
			'False Positive. Access to lsass.exe was performed by svchost.exe under NT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM, with services.exe as the parent process. There is no evidence of a dump, mimikatz, suspicious PowerShell, or comsvcs.dll. The activity matches normal system behavior.',
		kql: 'host.name: "VEGA-WS" and event.code: "10" and target.process.name: "lsass.exe"',
		events: 'AUR-EVT-000051',
	},
];
---

<section class="alert-practice" data-alert-practice>
	<div class="practice-header">
		<div class="score-box" data-score>Progress: 0 / {alerts.length}</div>
	</div>

	<div class="carousel-shell">
		<div class="carousel-status">
			<span data-carousel-position>Question 1 / {alerts.length}</span>
			<div class="progress-track" aria-hidden="true">
				<span data-progress-bar style={`width: ${100 / alerts.length}%`}></span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="alerts-carousel" data-carousel>
			{
				alerts.map((alert, index) => (
					<article
						class:list={['alert-card', index === 0 && 'is-active']}
						data-alert-card
						data-alert-id={alert.id}
						data-correct={alert.correct}
						hidden={index !== 0}
					>
						<div class="alert-card-header">
							<span class="alert-number">{alert.code}</span>
							<h3>{alert.title}</h3>
						</div>

						<div class="options" role="radiogroup" aria-label={`Classification for ${alert.code}`}>
							<label>
								<input
									type="radio"
									name={`alert-${alert.id}`}
									value="true"
									data-option
								/>
								True Positive
							</label>

							<label>
								<input
									type="radio"
									name={`alert-${alert.id}`}
									value="false"
									data-option
								/>
								False Positive
							</label>
						</div>

						<div class="actions">
							<button type="button" class="check-button" data-check>
								Check Answer
							</button>

							<button type="button" class="reset-button" data-reset>
								Reset
							</button>
						</div>

						<p class="result-message" data-result hidden></p>

						<details class="explanation-box" data-explanation hidden>
							<summary>View Explanation and Evidence</summary>

							<div class="explanation-content">
								<strong>Explanation:</strong>
								<p>{alert.explanation}</p>

								<strong>Recommended KQL:</strong>
								<pre><code>{alert.kql}</code></pre>

								<strong>Related Events:</strong>
								<p>{alert.events}</p>
							</div>
						</details>
					</article>
				))
			}
		</div>

		<div class="carousel-controls" aria-label="Carousel controls">
			<button type="button" class="nav-button" data-prev aria-label="Previous question">
				<span aria-hidden="true">&larr;</span>
				Previous
			</button>

			<div class="dot-list" data-dot-list aria-label="Select question">
				{
					alerts.map((alert, index) => (
						<button
							type="button"
							class:list={['dot-button', index === 0 && 'is-active']}
							data-dot={index}
							aria-label={`Go to question ${alert.id}`}
							aria-current={index === 0 ? 'step' : undefined}
						>
							{alert.id}
						</button>
					))
				}
			</div>

			<button type="button" class="nav-button" data-next aria-label="Next question">
				Next
				<span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
			</button>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<script>
	const practiceSections = document.querySelectorAll('[data-alert-practice]');

	practiceSections.forEach((section) => {
		const cards = Array.from(section.querySelectorAll('[data-alert-card]'));
		const scoreBox = section.querySelector('[data-score]');
		const positionBox = section.querySelector('[data-carousel-position]');
		const progressBar = section.querySelector('[data-progress-bar]');
		const prevButton = section.querySelector('[data-prev]');
		const nextButton = section.querySelector('[data-next]');
		const dots = Array.from(section.querySelectorAll('[data-dot]'));
		let currentIndex = 0;

		function updateScore() {
			const completed = cards.filter((card) => card.dataset.completed === 'true').length;

			if (scoreBox) {
				scoreBox.textContent = `Progress: ${completed} / ${cards.length}`;
			}
		}

		function showCard(index) {
			currentIndex = Math.max(0, Math.min(index, cards.length - 1));

			cards.forEach((card, cardIndex) => {
				const isActive = cardIndex === currentIndex;
				card.hidden = !isActive;
				card.classList.toggle('is-active', isActive);
			});

			dots.forEach((dot, dotIndex) => {
				const isActive = dotIndex === currentIndex;
				dot.classList.toggle('is-active', isActive);
				dot.setAttribute('aria-current', isActive ? 'step' : 'false');
			});

			if (positionBox) {
				positionBox.textContent = `Question ${currentIndex + 1} / ${cards.length}`;
			}

			if (progressBar) {
				progressBar.style.width = `${((currentIndex + 1) / cards.length) * 100}%`;
			}

			if (prevButton) {
				prevButton.disabled = currentIndex === 0;
			}

			if (nextButton) {
				nextButton.disabled = currentIndex === cards.length - 1;
			}
		}

		cards.forEach((card) => {
			const alertId = card.dataset.alertId;
			const correctAnswer = card.dataset.correct;
			const checkButton = card.querySelector('[data-check]');
			const resetButton = card.querySelector('[data-reset]');
			const result = card.querySelector('[data-result]');
			const explanation = card.querySelector('[data-explanation]');
			const options = Array.from(card.querySelectorAll('[data-option]'));
			const storageKey = `aurelius-alert-${alertId}`;
			const savedAnswer = localStorage.getItem(storageKey);

			if (savedAnswer) {
				const savedOption = card.querySelector(`input[value="${savedAnswer}"]`);

				if (savedOption) {
					savedOption.checked = true;
				}
			}

			checkButton?.addEventListener('click', () => {
				const selected = card.querySelector('input[type="radio"]:checked');

				if (!selected) {
					if (result) {
						result.hidden = false;
						result.textContent =
							'Select True Positive or False Positive before checking your answer.';
						result.className = 'result-message warning';
					}

					if (explanation) {
						explanation.hidden = true;
					}

					return;
				}

				localStorage.setItem(storageKey, selected.value);
				card.dataset.completed = 'true';

				const isCorrect = selected.value === correctAnswer;

				if (result) {
					result.hidden = false;
					result.textContent = isCorrect
						? 'Correct.'
						: 'Incorrect. Review the explanation.';
					result.className = isCorrect
						? 'result-message correct'
						: 'result-message incorrect';
				}

				if (explanation) {
					explanation.hidden = false;
					explanation.open = false;
				}

				options.forEach((option) => {
					option.disabled = true;
				});

				updateScore();
			});

			resetButton?.addEventListener('click', () => {
				localStorage.removeItem(storageKey);
				card.dataset.completed = 'false';

				options.forEach((option) => {
					option.checked = false;
					option.disabled = false;
				});

				if (result) {
					result.hidden = true;
					result.textContent = '';
					result.className = 'result-message';
				}

				if (explanation) {
					explanation.hidden = true;
					explanation.open = false;
				}

				updateScore();
			});
		});

		prevButton?.addEventListener('click', () => {
			showCard(currentIndex - 1);
		});

		nextButton?.addEventListener('click', () => {
			showCard(currentIndex + 1);
		});

		dots.forEach((dot) => {
			dot.addEventListener('click', () => {
				showCard(Number(dot.dataset.dot));
			});
		});

		section.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
			if (event.key === 'ArrowLeft') {
				showCard(currentIndex - 1);
			}

			if (event.key === 'ArrowRight') {
				showCard(currentIndex + 1);
			}
		});

		updateScore();
		showCard(0);
	});
</script>

<style>
	.alert-practice {
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.alert-practice [hidden] {
		display: none !important;
	}

	.practice-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.practice-header h2 {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.practice-header p {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		opacity: 0.7;
	}

	.score-box {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.5);
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.carousel-shell {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1rem;
	}

	.carousel-status {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.progress-track {
		overflow: hidden;
		width: 100%;
		height: 0.55rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.2);
	}

	.progress-track span {
		display: block;
		height: 100%;
		border-radius: inherit;
		background: #38bdf8;
		transition: width 180ms ease;
	}

	.alerts-carousel {
		position: relative;
		min-height: 18rem;
	}

	.alert-card {
		border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.35);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1rem;
		background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04);
	}

	.alert-card.is-active {
		animation: fade-slide 180ms ease;
	}

	.alert-card-header {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.4rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
	}

	.alert-number {
		display: inline-flex;
		width: fit-content;
		padding: 0.35rem 0.55rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.35);
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		line-height: 1;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	.alert-card h3 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1.18rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		line-height: 1.25;
		overflow-wrap: anywhere;
	}

	.options {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin: 0.85rem 0;
	}

	.options label {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.4rem;
		min-height: 2.5rem;
		padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.35);
		border-radius: 8px;
		cursor: pointer;
	}

	.options input {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.actions,
	.carousel-controls {
		display: flex;
